<% content_for :title, "Your organizations" %>

<div class="w-full max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Your organizations</h1>
    <%= button_to "Log out", logout_path, method: :delete, class: "text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800" %>
  </div>

  <% if @organizations.blank? %>
    <p class="text-gray-500">You don't belong to any HCB organizations yet.</p>
  <% else %>
    <ul class="divide-y divide-gray-200 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
      <% @organizations.each do |org| %>
        <li>
          <%= link_to organization_matcher_path(organization_id: org["slug"] || org["id"]),
                class: "flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 hover:bg-gray-50" do %>
            <span class="font-medium"><%= org["name"] %></span>
            <span class="text-gray-400">&rarr;</span>
          <% end %>
        </li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  <% end %>
</div>

<div>
<h2>
Disclaimer: This project was created by an HCB Ops contributor to match incoming and outgoing transactions in HCB clearinghouse, amongst other HCB internal organizations such as Unallocated Donations.

This project was created in one weekend by a very tired kid and is in no way guaranteed to be reliable (although this kid does use this program).

Also HCB v4 API is slow so there's not much I can do about that either :( (I tried loading transactions as soon as I received each page in an organization).

<br><br>

Also, I do apologize for the lack of styling - the minimalistic and sometimes visually appealing CSS is <i>totally</i> intentional.
</h2>
</div>
